Cell.Text: There's some trouble in Eastmarch. Farmers are being menaced by some bad types who've built up a stronghold in the area.
There's some trouble in Falkreath. There's always some sort of trouble down there, but now it's come to a head.
There's some trouble in Haafingar. The Legion's too busy with the war, and they're hiring us to take care of some local trouble.
We've been hired to deal with some pests in Hjaalmarch. Someone's got them riled up, and you need to put an end to it.
There's some trouble in The Pale. We need you to go in and clear out an enemy stronghold.
There's always some sort of trouble in The Reach, but a local warlord has raised the stakes. We have to handle the situation.
The Rift is seeing a lot of trouble from some riff-raff. We need to head in and break them up.
We've got trouble right here in Whiterun Hold. Just a local warlord causing problems - nothing we can't handle.
There's trouble up in Winterhold. I'm a little surprised anyone's complaining about it, but a contract is a contract.
Nothing but a bunch of lowly bandits. They are cowards. You should be able to scatter them with little effort.
You're entering a crypt filled with the restless dead. Not pretty, but if you don't stop them, they'll move on to the locals.
The Falmer. There have been reports that they've been attacking people at night.
It's a problem with the Forsworn. Unpredictable, unknowable, and dangerous. Be cautious.
It's a clan of giants. The war is driving them out of their lands, and they've started attacking settlements.
You'll be clearing out a nest of those Hagravens. I've never faced one myself, but I hear... disturbing things about them.
Oddly enough, Spriggans. They normally stay away from other creatures, but for some reason, this particular grove isn't.
Bloodsuckers. Vampires. Take every precaution. One bite, and you could end up as one of them.
Warlocks. I've never trusted those who meddle with magicka. The Mages Guild is bad enough. Destroy these rogues.

Node.Caption: CR05EnemyTypeTopic: What kind of trouble should I expect?

Cell.Text: G|I knew you could be counted on. Do what must be done.
G|Excellent. Show them no mercy.
G|Good. Do not spare them your blade.
G|Such is your choice. The contract will remain open for the time being.
G|Shame. But, I'm certain that one of the younger Companions will take up this contract.
G|Very well. The contract will be available until someone else picks it up.
G|And I have already received word that the client is satisfied. You have done well for yourself, and for the Companions.
G|Another job well done. Your payment is secure, and you have my thanks.
G|I expected no less of you. And once again, you have not disappointed.
